title: Video shows corrections officer drop transgender woman on her face in Baltimore corrections facility
description: Video of a transgender woman being held in a chokehold by a Baltimore corrections officer, then dropped on her face and dragged, was released by her attorney as part of a civil lawsuit against the state and several of the officers allegedly involved.

title: Trump loses bid to shield White House records from House Jan. 6 committee
Brooke Shields on her Barbara Walters interview: 'It's not journalism'
description: In an episode of Dax Shepard's "Armchair Expert" podcast, actress Brooke Shields discussed her experience being interviewed by Barbara Walters as a teenager.

title: Reality TV star found guilty of child pornography
description: A jury on Thursday found reality TV star Josh Duggar guilty of receipt of child pornography and possession of child pornography, according to the judgement filed in the United States District Court Western District of Arkansas Fayetteville Division.

title: Cuban activist's dramatic departure divides supporters
description: Cuban activist and playwright Yunior Garcia talks to CNN's Isa Soares about his controversial decision to flee to Spain.

title: Someone just paid $7,753 for school papers graded by Elon Musk
description: Today, a lot of business students would probably pay serious money for Elon Musk's opinion of their work. In 1995, though -- long before he took control of Tesla and, later, founded SpaceX -- Musk was a teaching assistant helping grade exams and papers at the University of Pennsylvania's famous Wharton School of Business.

title: Why it matters that the Trump White House lied about the President's Covid case
description: When former President Trump contracted Covid-19 last fall, the world recorded his every move... and it turns out the information being put out from his White House grossly downplayed the severity of his condition. In the latest episode of The Point, CNN's Chris Cillizza discusses why these new revelations still matter as Trump's grip on the GOP remains strong.

title: Volkswagen increases spending on EVs to $100 billion
description: More than half the money Volkswagen Group spends in the next five years will go towards electric vehicles and other high-technology efforts, the German automaker announced Thursday.

title: Rocketing 300mph through the skies with nothing but a parachute: Welcome to speed skydiving
description: The next time you're in a car traveling along the freeway at 70 miles per hour, see what it feels like when you thrust your hand out of the window -- it's an intense sensation.

title: Reggae legend Robbie Shakespeare dies aged 68
description: Robbie Shakespeare, the legendary bass player and one half of the band Sly and Robbie, has died at the age of 68.

title: CEO turned company into a culture-war lightning rod by giving extremists a platform
description: In October of 2018, a man walked into the Tree of Life synagogue in Pittsburgh and opened fire, killing 11 people -- the worst anti-Semitic attack in US history. The suspected shooter had been a serial poster of genocidal rantings about Jews on a social platform called Gab.

title: Radio host asked Trump if he'd run for president in 2024. Hear his reply
description: Former President Donald Trump did an extended interview with conservative talk radio host Hugh Hewitt, who asked him whether he would run for president a third time in 2024. Hear Trump's reply.

title: Camels ejected from beauty contest over Botox use and other 'tampering'
description: Organizers of a popular camel beauty contest in Saudi Arabia have disqualified 43 contestants after cracking down on Botox injections and other forms of "tampering" by breeders.

title: New Zealand plans to ban smoking for the next generation
description: New Zealand plans to outlaw smoking for the next generation so they will never be legally able to buy tobacco in the country.

title: Commander of Navy SEAL Team 8 dies in training accident
description: The commander of the US Navy's SEAL Team 8 died Tuesday from injuries sustained in a training accident in Virginia Beach over the weekend, the Navy said.

title: Cardi B shares bizarre snack idea with followers
description: Rapper Cardi B shared a video with fans promoting dipping nacho cheese Doritos in barbeque sauce.

title: Chelsea star Sam Kerr barges pitch invader to the ground, gets yellow card in Women's Champions League game
description: Sam Kerr knocked a pitch invader to the ground on Wednesday evening during Chelsea's 0-0 draw with Juventus in the Women's Champions League and was shown a yellow card for it afterwards.

title: Boris Johnson's bad week isn't getting any better
Woman pulled from submerged car near brink of Niagara Falls has died, police say
description: A woman who was pulled from a car submerged in rushing water near the brink of Niagara Falls has died, New York State Park Police said Wednesday.

title: Aide arrested after bringing gun to US Capitol complex
description: The Longworth House Office Building of the US Capitol complex was put on a shelter-in-place order after a Capitol staffer brought a gun into the building, multiple sources told CNN.

title: China's Evergrande has defaulted on its debt
description: Evergrande, the embattled Chinese property developer, has defaulted on its debt, according to Fitch Ratings.

title: 'Democracy needs champions:' Biden kicks off first 'Summit for Democracy' at White House
Hear why these real estate agents are selling homes on TikTok
description: CNN Business talked with real estate agents on the app to figure out why, in the midst of a pandemic, they turned to the unconventional method of using TikTok to find clientele, sell property, and more.

title: Sole survivor of India helicopter crash fights for his life as country mourns victims
description: The only survivor of a helicopter crash that killed 13 people including India's top military official is on life support, officials said Thursday, as the nation mourned the victims and investigations into the incident continued.

title: Didi is leaving Wall Street. A 'perfect storm' means other Chinese tech stocks may follow
description: Chinese ride-hailing giant Didi wants to bail on Wall Street. It may soon have plenty of company.

title: The hunt for new Covid-19 variants
EU wants to give millions of gig economy workers paid leave and a minimum wage
description: As many as four million European gig economy workers could become employees if new draft EU legislation becomes law.

title: Canada bans conversion therapy, a practice Trudeau calls 'despicable and degrading'
description: Canada on Wednesday banned conversion therapy, which are treatments that claim to be able to change a person's sexual orientation or identity.

title: Finland's Prime Minister apologizes for not isolating after nightclub photo surfaces
description: Finnish Prime Minister Sanna Marin apologized to the public on Wednesday after a photo surfaced of her in a nightclub following the foreign minister testing positive for Covid-19.

title: Cream cheese shortage hits famous New York cheesecake shop
description: Junior's Cheesecake has a big problem: Not enough cream cheese.

title: Sweden reclaims place names from IKEA
description: Bolmen: your toilet brush. Toftan: your trash can. Misterhult: your bamboo lamp. Those exotic-sounding names that IKEA gives your household products are familiar words to Swedish speakers -- often, they're named after famous destinations.

title: The cannons keeping airplanes safe, one chicken at a time
description: Birds may be the undisputed masters of the air, but they've been at the losing end of airborne collisions since the dawn of aviation in 1905, when pioneer pilot Orville Wright reported the first bird strike.
